1 A RESOLUTION expressing support for the mission and work of the Consumer
2 Financial Protection Bureau.
3 WHEREAS, following the most severe financial crisis since the Great Depression,
4 Congress passed the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act in
5 2010, which created the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB);
6 WHEREAS, the CFPB was created as a single point of accountability for enforcing
7 federal consumer financial protection laws and protecting consumers in the financial
8 marketplace;
9 WHEREAS, the work of the CFPB includes rooting out unfair, deceptive, or
10 abusive acts and practices by writing rules, supervising companies, and enforcing the
11 law;
12 WHEREAS, the CFPB enforces laws that outlaw discrimination in consumer
13 finance;
14 WHEREAS, the CFPB takes consumer complaints and has sent over 6.8 million
15 consumer complaints to companies for responses;
16 WHEREAS, over 21 billion dollars in monetary compensation, principal
17 reductions, canceled debts, and other consumer relief has resulted from CFPB
18 enforcement and supervisory work;
19 WHEREAS, 363 million dollars in monetary relief has resulted from 39
20 enforcement actions involving servicemembers and veterans, including six enforcement
21 actions for violations of the Military Lending Act;
22 WHEREAS, the CFPB enhances financial education, researches consumer
23 experiences relating to the use of financial products, and monitors financial markets for
24 new risks to consumers;
25 WHEREAS, over five billion dollars in civil monetary penalties have been imposed
26 by the CFPB against companies and individuals that violate the law; and
27 WHEREAS, the CFPB serves an important role in protecting consumers, veterans,
